  I.6: { rating: "PARTIALLY", reason: "Make is richly documented, but comparable free depth that also treats just and deterministic orchestration as a coherent topic is more fragmented." }
  I.7: { rating: "WIDELY", reason: "Git internals are unusually well served by free resources, especially official docs and openly available book-length explanations." }
  I.8: { rating: "PARTIALLY", reason: "Each observability tool is documented, but a unified operational guide to process observation across strace, ltrace, lsof, and ss is less common." }
  I.9: { rating: "WIDELY", reason: "Container internals have strong free coverage from kernel-focused blog posts, conference talks, and deep technical explainers." }
  I.10: { rating: "PARTIALLY", reason: "The individual tools are well covered, but equivalent depth across curl, TLS inspection, DNS, packet capture, and firewalling usually requires stitching sources together." }
  I.11: { rating: "PARTIALLY", reason: "systemd, cron, and supervisord are each documented, but cross-tool guidance on supervising agent processes is less centralized." }
  I.12: { rating: "WIDELY", reason: "Advanced bash topics are supported by the Bash manual, Wooledge resources, and many detailed free examples." }

  II.1: { rating: "WIDELY", reason: "Transformer basics and operational consequences are now well explained in free papers, talks, visual explainers, and engineering blogs." }
